Items.Title: Oversight - HRA  -  The End of Welfare?  New York City After Welfare Time Limits.
Items.MinutesNote:
Adjourned until May 7, 2001 - Two motions were approved by the Committee by votes of 6 to 1.  

The motions were:  

1.  To compel the appearance of Jason Turner, Commissioner of the Human Resources Administration before the Committee on General Welfare on May 7, 2001 at 10:00 a.m.; and

2.  In the event the Commissioner fails to appear before the Committee on General Welfare on May 7, 2001 at 10:00 a.m., to issue a subpoena compelling his appearance.
